{% block system %}
You are a CAFM document data extraction specialist.
Extract structured CAFM-relevant data from Word documents containing maintenance records,
inspection reports, or operational notes.
Return ONLY valid JSON — no markdown, no explanation.
{% endblock %}

{% block user %}
Extract all CAFM-relevant data from the following Word document.

Document: {{ source_filename }}
{% if pass_number and total_passes %}Pass {{ pass_number }} of {{ total_passes }}.{% endif %}
{% if retry_context %}Correct this error from the previous attempt: {{ retry_context }}{% endif %}
{% if previous_contradictions %}
Contradictions to resolve:
{% for issue in previous_contradictions %}- {{ issue }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

Return a JSON object with EXACTLY this structure:

{
  "document_type": "inspection_report | maintenance_record | work_order | procedure | other",
  "title": "string or null",
  "date": "YYYY-MM-DD or null",
  "author": "string or null",
  "site_location": "string or null",
  "assets": [
    {
      "asset_code": "string or null",
      "asset_name": "string or null",
      "category": "string or null",
      "observations": "string or null"
    }
  ],
  "work_orders": [
    {
      "wo_code": "string or null",
      "description": "string or null",
      "priority": "Highest | High | Medium | Low | Lowest | null",
      "status": "Open | Closed | null"
    }
  ],
  "findings": [
    {
      "section": "string or null",
      "finding_type": "string",
      "description": "string",
      "risk_level": "High | Medium | Low",
      "requires_corrective_action": false
    }
  ],
  "raw_tables": [],
  "confidence_per_field": {
    "document_type": "high | medium | low",
    "date": "high | medium | low"
  }
}

Rules:
- Identify document_type from the content and structure.
- Extract ALL tables as raw_tables (list of row-dicts) if they contain structured data
  not captured in the typed arrays above.
- Findings: one object per distinct finding or observation.
- Use null for missing fields; [] for empty lists.
- Dates in YYYY-MM-DD format.
{% endblock %}
